The '''1952 Kentucky Wildcats football team''' represented the [[University of Kentucky]] in the [[1952 college football season]]. The Wildcats scored 181 points while allowing 180 points. Kentucky finished the season ranked #20 in the final [[AP Poll]].<ref>[http://www.appollarchive.com/football/ap/seasons.cfm?seasonid=1952 Final 1952 AP poll at AP Poll Archive]</ref> It was the seventh consecutive winning season for the Wildcats with [[Bear Bryant]] as the head coach.<ref>http://cfreference.net/cfr/coach.s?id=438</ref>
==Season== *In the Border Battle, [[Tennessee Volunteers football|Tennessee]] and Kentucky tied, and Tennessee kept the Beer Barrel as the they had won the previous year.<ref>http://mcubed.net/ncaaf/series/tn/ky.shtml</ref>
